\title{News for Package 'sylly'}
\encoding{UTF-8}
\section{Changes in sylly version 0.1-5 (2018-07-29)}{
  \subsection{fixed}{
    \itemize{
      \item \code{sylly:::sylly_langpack()}: removed obsolete 'flattr_user' attribute
    }
  }
  \subsection{changed}{
    \itemize{
      \item session settings done with \code{set.sylly.env()} or queried by \code{get.sylly.env()}
        are no longer stored in an internal environment but the global .Options;
        this also allows for setting defaults in an .Rprofile file using \code{options()}
      \item vignette is now in RMarkdown/HTML format; the SWeave/PDF version was
        dropped; it was also updated and has a new section on caching
      \item \code{sylly:::sylly_langpack()}: updated the README.md template
      \item \code{sylly:::sylly_langpack()}: removed "\\dontrun\{\}" from generated example
        section
      \item in the docs, improved the link format for classes, omitting the "-class"
        suffix
    }
  }
  \subsection{added}{
    \itemize{
      \item new functions \code{available.sylly.lang()} and \code{install.sylly.lang()} to
        comfortably install language packages
      \item new class object contructors \code{kRp_hyphen()} and \code{kRp_hyph_pat()} can be used
        instead of new(\code{"kRp.hyphen"}, ...) etc.
    }
  }
}
